	   <a name=101612102731532></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101612102731532><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>An Epic-ized DoRF!</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>397 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 14th 10:52 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings fellow Paladins,<br><br>Back on November 24th I posted a step by step run-down of what I had completed on my epic.&nbsp;&nbsp;This involved all the steps up to the Plane of Sky turn-in required on the 4th island for the Fiery Avenger, etc. etc.  That post is here:<br><br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/classes.html?class=6&amp;mid=100666076140748" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/classes.html?class=6&amp;mid=100666076140748</a><br><br>Well, last night I finally got my chance to complete my epic.  It's been a long time, but I've had good weapons so I didn't really feel the need to get my epic...but that's all behind me now!<br><br>However, there were some things NOT listed on the THREE different step by step guides for getting my epic that I had laid out before me...so I thought I would run the steps down here, picking up from my previous post linked above.<br><br>1) I eventually went to the Hole and killed the Keeper of Tombs for the Tainted Sword drop. Nothing really unusual about this. It just takes 2+ good groups to get there and do it...depending on group level.<br><br>2) I killed Kirak Vil in Nektulos Forest. Level 55 SK, pretty tough but did it with one group.<br><br>3) I now had all the pieces needed for my epic:<br><br>- A Ghoulbane<br>- A Soulfire<br>- Lich Miraguls Robe<br>- Lich Miraguls Head<br>These are for the Fiery Avenger given in Sky<br><br>- A purified Shield originally from Kirak vil<br>- A purified Sword originally from The Keeper of Tombs<br>- A purified Breastplate originally from a Thought Corrupter in Plane of Hate<br>These are for the Fiery Defender turn-in in Fear<br><br>I did the turn-ins with the Sword, Shield and Breastplate to Gnallen in Erudin as outlined in the instructions on my sheets and I got the Mark of Atonement.  So far so good...everything according to plan and my sheets.<br><br>Last night I went to the Plane of Sky (commonly called the Plane of Air).  This is a VERY cool zone, but not for the noobie PoA raider.  It's difficult to know what to do, what key to use, to get from island to island, etc.  Fortunately I had an experienced raiding group of 24 folks.<br><br>We moved to island 4, killing as we went.  I prepared for my hand in to Inte Akira inside the tower on the 4th island.  A wizard ported up to island 1 to give the 500 plat to Dirkog Steelhand in the Quest Hall to spawn Inte...just like the spoiler sheets said. Piece of cake, right? WRONG!<br><br>Dirkog isn't up...he tells me!! OMG!! Panic, Panic, Panic.  Turns out...you have SPAWN DIRKOG to give him the 500 plat to SPAWN Inte!! OMG!! No one told me that! What's up with that??? Panic, Panic, Panic.  Well, I sent out some tells in a rush, got some vague descriptions of how to do this, relayed all that to my wizard on the first island through tells and Guild chat, and he began hailing NPC's in the Quest Hall.  He eventually found one that mentioned Dirkog.  This NPC gave my wizard friend a BOOK! OMG, a BOOK??? What Book?? There's no Book!! My sheets don't say anyting about a Book!!  What do I do with a BOOK??? Panic...Panic...Panic. <br><br>As I scrambled through my sheets, reading and looking for information on some Book about &quot;Walking with Evil&quot;...I find nothing.  It's not mentioned. Spawning Dirkog wasn't mentioned and this book is not mentioned. OMG!! Meanwhile I have 23 Guild Raiders sitting around watching and waiting for me to get on with it.  I decide to take a chance and tell my wizard friend to give the Book back to the NPC. My heart is pounding, I'm sweating, and the butterflies in my stomach have turned into Teradactyls!  He gives the book to the NPC and BINGO, Dirkog Spawns.  THANK GOD!! He gives Dirkog the 500 plat and Inte Akira spawns right in front of me and sits down. My worries are over.<br><br>I conned Inte real quick to make sure I was Ally, hailed him which caused him to stand, then turned in my Ghoulbane...he gave me back the Blessing. I turned in my Soulfire...he gave me the Blessing.  I turned in BOTH Blessings, the Head of Lich Miragul and his Robe ALL AT ONCE and TADA!!!! The Fiery Avenger.<br><br>Compared to what I went through in the Plane of Sky, the turn in to Irak Altil in the Plane of Fear was anti-climactic.  Another guild had cleared Fear that very night so it was simple. A druid ported me to Feerrot. We zoned into the Plane of Fear (which was barren and desolate except for Cazic Thule stompin around).  He used track and led me straight to Irak Altil. I turned in the Mark of Atonement from the Breastplate, Shield and Sword pre-epic quests that I got from Gnallen in Erudin AND the Fiery Avenger ALL AT ONCE, and...<br><br>I am now the proud wielder of the Fiery Defender...Paladin Epic! <br><br>I can laugh about it today...but the Spawning of Dirkog Steelhand and the Book caught me COMPLETELY by surprise...and I thought I was well prepared.  All in all...I'm certainly glad I have my epic now and it will become my main weapon...at least until I complete the Spirit of Gazicor quest! <br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>&quot;Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness&quot;<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
